1a) If you are using this layout:
./mediawiki/extensions/{A,B,C}

Go to mediawiki directory and extract the release file:
tar xjf MediaWikiLanguageExtensionBundle-VERSION.tar.bz2

Your extension variable is
$EXT = "$IP/extensions";

1b) If you are using this layout:
./mediawiki/
./extensions/{A,B,C}

Go to common parent directory and extract the release file:
tar xjf MediaWikiLanguageExtensionBundle-VERSION.tar.bz2

Your extension variables are:
$EXT = "$IP/../extensions";
$wgExtensionAssetsPath = "{$wgScriptPath}/../extensions";

2) Add/update your LocalSettings.php. Near the end, place the config lines
given above followed by this:

require_once( "$EXT/Babel/Babel.php" );
require_once( "$EXT/cldr/cldr.php" );
require_once( "$EXT/Translate/Translate.php" );
$wgGroupPermissions['user']['translate'] = true;
$wgGroupPermissions['user']['translate-messagereview'] = true;
$wgGroupPermissions['user']['translate-groupreview'] = true;
$wgGroupPermissions['user']['translate-import'] = true;
$wgGroupPermissions['sysop']['pagetranslation'] = true;
$wgGroupPermissions['sysop']['translate-manage'] = true;
$wgTranslateDocumentationLanguageCode = 'qqq';
require_once( "$EXT/UniversalLanguageSelector/UniversalLanguageSelector.php" );

3a) Update database tables from the command line. In the directory where your
LocalSettings.php is located, run the following command:
php maintenance/update.php

3b) Update database tables from the web. Go to example.com/mediawiki/mw-config/
by using your domain and path and rerun install.
